data.name: label5.Text
data.value:
- In the upper right-hand corner, there are buttons for Instructions when you are in a task, Help on the main page, and the gear for settings visible on all pages. ~ Note: You are currently in the Help section
- On the main page, below each Task section is a checklist of the sub-tasks. They will be checked off once you have correctly completed that whole sub-section.
- The Instructions Tab, shown on task pages, indicates how each task section should be completed according to the handbook.
- In settings, you may change the accessibility and reset your progress which will erase all your progress and uploads
- The review button can be assessed [when…/ at any time] and will generate a complete checklist report for each task and sub-task section in detail.
-[how each tab on a task works] -[review section]
